This paper focuses on the initial cell search procedure in mmWave networks, which is a key aspect of network communication and falls under the category of network infrastructure (NI). The paper also involves the analysis of performance in terms of latency and failure probability, which is related to information theory (IT) and systems and control (SY). Additionally, the use of directional transmissions and stochastic geometry framework relates to the category of multimedia (MM) and communication (COM).
